  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Arlberg Austrian Twins</strong> are around 25m² and can sleep up to three (extra bed is a single sofa bed). These rooms have an ensuite with bath.</p>
<p><strong>Omeshorn Junior Suites</strong> are around 36m² and can sleep two to four people (extra bed is a double sofa bed). These rooms have a lounge area, balcony, and ensuite with bath.</p>
<p><strong>Schafberg Junior Suites</strong> are around 41m² and can sleep up to four people (extra bed is a double sofa bed). These rooms have a lounge area, south-facing balcony, espresso machine, and ensuite with bath.</p>
<p><strong>Seekopf Junior Suites</strong> are even larger at around 45m². These rooms sleep up to four people (extra bed is a double sofa bed) and have a lounge area, south-facing balcony, espresso machine, and an ensuite with bath and separate shower.</p>
<p><strong>Lechtal Single Room</strong>s are around 15m² and have an ensuite with shower.</p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Minibar</li>
<li>Bathrobes</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>General information</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Check-in: <strong>2pm</strong></li>
<li>Check-out: <strong>11am</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees and taxes</strong></p>
<p>A resort tourist tax of approx. €3.80 per person per night is payable locally (this will be approx. €4.60 per person per night for Summer 25). Children under 14 years are exempt.</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>]]></roomsDescription>
